<ItacAcademyItem AcademyId="0108" RecordId="021-000005055"><Name>Vignaiuoli (Accademia dei)</Name><City CityId="45"><CityItalianName>Roma</CityItalianName><CityEnglishName>Rome</CityEnglishName><CityLatinName>Romae</CityLatinName></City><StartDate>1527/30</StartDate><EndDate>1538?</EndDate><DateText>1527/30-1538?</DateText><Notes>Sources for the list of members of this Academy, are the following documents: the letter by Berni to Bini (Florence 12 April 1534), in Lettere facete et piacevoli ... raccolte da m. Dionigi Atanagi, libro primo (Venice: B. Zaltieri, 1561), p. 48; the dedication of Equicola Institutioni by Marco Sabino to Uberto Strozzi;  another letter by Mauro D`Arcano to Gandolfo Porrino (16 dic. 1531), in Lettere facete et piacevoli... (Venice: B. Zaltieri, 1561), pp. 319-323, See also Gianni Ballistreri, `Bini, Giovan Francesco`, in DBI, Paola Cosentino, `L`Accademia della Virtu`, dicerie e cicalate di Annibal Caro e di altri virtuosi`, in Cum notibusse et commentaribusse..., ed. Paolo Procaccioli, Manziana 2001, and Franco Pignatti, `Molza, Francesco Maria`, in DBI. Cosentino disagrees that Mauro`s letter to Porrino should be seen as a source related to this Academy.</Notes><ItacPersonItem PersonId="18170" RecordId="022-000005139"><Name>Berni,Francesco,,</Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="18128" RecordId="022-000005090"><Name>Bini,Giovan Francesco,,1480s - 1556</Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="18090" RecordId="022-000005043"><Name>Molza,Francesco Maria,,1489 - 1544</Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="15057" RecordId="022-000001098"><Name>Mauro,Francesco,,</Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="16557" RecordId="022-000003270"><Name>Della Casa,Giovanni,Archbishop of Benevento,1503 - 1556</Name><Nickname /><Motto /